# .dockerignore — keep secrets + build noise out of the Docker build context (HR-1, §D-002).
# SDD-PROVENANCE: U-004 | vault: .mega-sdd/vaults/api-platform
#
# Build strategy: Option A (pre-built JAR). The Dockerfile COPIES the host-built
# JAR from target/, so the JAR MUST be in the build context. Everything else
# under target/ (class files, surefire reports, maven-status) is excluded.
#
# Excluded: secrets (.env), target/ build noise (EXCEPT the pre-built JAR),
# VCS/IDE state, host-only launchers. KEPT: .env.example (template, not secret),
# pom.xml, mvnw, mvnw.cmd, .mvn/, src/, Dockerfile, target/*.jar (pre-built).

# Exclude all of target/ then re-include the pre-built JAR (Option A needs it).
target/*
!target/coresystembackend-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar
.git/
.gitignore
.mega-sdd/
.idea/
.vscode/
*.log
*.log.*
node_modules/
preview.webp
run-app.sh
docs/
.env
.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar
docker-compose.yml
